lspace:0;mso-table-rspace:0;mso-hide:all;display:none;max-height:0;overflow:hidden;border-radius:0;color:#000;width:630px;margin:0 auto\" width=\"630\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"column column-1\" width=\"100%\" style=\"mso-table-lspace:0;mso-table-rspace:0;font-weight:400;text-align:left;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;vertical-align:top\"><table class=\"image_block block-1\" width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" role=\"presentation\" \r\nstyle=\"mso-table-lspace:0;mso-table-rspace:0;mso-hide:all;display:none;max-height:0;overflow:hidden\"><tr><td class=\"pad\" style=\"width:100%;padding-right:0;padding-left:0\"><div class=\"alignment\" align=\"center\"><div style=\"max-width:236px\"><a href=\"https://link.theatlantic.com/click/45327773.55622/aHR0cHM6Ly9hY2NvdW50cy50aGVhdGxhbnRpYy5jb20vcHJvZHVjdHMvP3V0bV9tZWRpdW09Y3ImdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1lbWFpbA/668d137112b797104109b7bcEcd65f710\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://media.sailthru.com/fss/flhesy/85caf798-3b4b-446c-932d-fca54157f28d/Frame+448+%283%29_62lf.png\" style=\"display:block;height:auto;border:0;width:100%\" width=\"236\" \r\nalt=\"\" title=\"\" height=\"auto\"></a></div></div></td></tr></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]--><table class=\"row row-5\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"mso-table-lspace:0;mso-table-rspace:0\"><tbody><tr><td><table class=\"row-content stack\" align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" role=\"presentation\" \r\nstyle=\"mso-table-lspace:0;mso-table-rspace:0;border-radius:0;color:#000;width:630px;margin:0 auto\" width=\"630\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"column column-1\" width=\"100%\" style=\"mso-table-lspace:0;mso-table-rspace:0;font-weight:400;text-align:left;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:40px;vertical-align:top\"><table class=\"text_block block-1\" width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"mso-table-lspace:0;mso-table-rspace:0;word-break:break-word\"><tr><td \r\nclass=\"pad\" style=\"padding-bottom:40px\"><div style=\"font-family:serif\"><div class style=\"font-size:14px;font-family:adobe-garamond-pro,Times New Roman,serif;mso-line-height-alt:21px;color:#21272c;line-height:1.5\"><p style=\"margin:0;font-size:18px;mso-line-height-alt:27px\">\r\n<span style=\"word-break: break-word; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>In this issue:</strong> Caity Weaver’s colossal undertaking to <a href=\"https://link.theatlantic.com/click/45327773.55622/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlYXRsYW50aWMuY29tL21hZ2F6aW5lLzIwMjYvMDUvYmVzdC1mcmVlLXJlc3RhdXJhbnQtYnJlYWQtYW1lcmljYS82ODY1ODIvP3V0bV9tZWRpdW09Y3ImdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1lbWFpbA/668d137112b797104109b7bcBa6e643cb\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #21272c;\" rel=\"noopener\">find the best free bread in America</a>. Laura Secor on the <a href=\"https://link.theatlantic.com/click/45327773.55622/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlYXRsYW50aWMuY29tL21hZ2F6aW5lLzIwMjYvMDUvaXJhbi11cy1pc3JhZWwtd2FyLWRlbW9jcmFjeS13b21lbi82ODY1ODMvP3V0bV9tZWRpdW09Y3ImdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1lbWFpbA/668d137112b797104109b7bcB605c53bf\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #21272c;\" rel=\"noopener\">heartbreak of hoping for a democratic Iran</a>. McKay Coppins on a <a href=\"https://link.theatlantic.com/click/45327773.55622/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlYXRsYW50aWMuY29tL21hZ2F6aW5lLzIwMjYvMDUvbWV4aWNvLWNhcnRlbC1sYS11bmlvbi10ZXBpdG8vNjg2NDUzLz91dG1fbWVkaXVtPWNyJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9ZW1haWw/668d137112b797104109b7bcBc919523e\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #21272c;\" rel=\"noopener\">secret sports tournament organized by Mexico’s biggest cartels</a>. David Brooks on <a href=\"https://link.theatlantic.com/click/45327773.55622/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlYXRsYW50aWMuY29tL21hZ2F6aW5lLzIwMjYvMDUvcmVhY3Rpb25hcnktdHJhZGl0aW9uYWxpc20td29ybGR2aWV3LzY4NjU5Ny8_dXRtX21lZGl1bT1jciZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWVtYWls/668d137112b797104109b7bcB14d0fe3e\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #21272c;\" rel=\"noopener\">why society feels like it’s running backwards in time</a>. Noah Hawley on <a href=\"https://link.theatlantic.com/click/45327773.55622/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlYXRsYW50aWMuY29tL21hZ2F6aW5lLzIwMjYvMDUvYmlsbGlvbmFpcmUtY29uc2VxdWVuY2UtZnJlZS1yZWFsaXR5LzY4NjU4OC8_dXRtX21lZGl1bT1jciZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWVtYWls/668d137112b797104109b7bcB68c0d1ab\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #21272c;\" rel=\"noopener\">how the world’s richest men left the world of consequences behind</a>.</span>\r\n</p><p style=\"margin:0;font-size:18px;mso-line-height-alt:21px\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"margin:0;font-size:18px;mso-line-height-alt:27px\">\r\n<span style=\"word-break: break-word; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Plus: </strong><a href=\"https://link.theatlantic.com/click/45327773.55622/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlYXRsYW50aWMuY29tL21hZ2F6aW5lLzIwMjYvMDUvZ2Vyb250b2NyYWN5LXdlYWx0aC1wb3dlci82ODY1ODUvP3V0bV9tZWRpdW09Y3ImdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1lbWFpbA/668d137112b797104109b7bcBa7ccb677\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #21272c;\" rel=\"noopener\">America’s gerontocracy</a>, and the challenges it will leave for younger generations. The <a href=\"https://link.theatlantic.com/click/45327773.55622/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlYXRsYW50aWMuY29tL21hZ2F6aW5lLzIwMjYvMDUvZGVhdGgtYmVyZWF2ZW1lbnQtbWF0ZXJuYWwtZ3JpZWYvNjg2NTkwLz91dG1fbWVkaXVtPWNyJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9ZW1haWw/668d137112b797104109b7bcB43e11aa1\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #21272c;\" rel=\"noopener\">powerful grief</a> of a mother losing her daughter. <a href=\"https://link.theatlantic.com/click/45327773.55622/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlYXRsYW50aWMuY29tL21hZ2F6aW5lLzIwMjYvMDUvbW9kZXJuLXNlbGYtaGVscC1zZXZlbi1kZWFkbHktc2lucy82ODY1NzcvP3V0bV9tZWRpdW09Y3ImdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1lbWFpbA/668d137112b797104109b7bcB0b5516c8\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #21272c;\" rel=\"noopener\">The eighth deadly sin</a>, and a book on the other seven. <a href=\"https://link.theatlantic.com/click/45327773.55622/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlYXRsYW50aWMuY29tL21hZ2F6aW5lLzIwMjYvMDUvYmxhY2stb3V0LWxvdWQtY29tZWR5LXJldmlldy82ODY1ODAvP3V0bV9tZWRpdW09Y3ImdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1lbWFpbA/668d137112b797104109b7bcB353eba90\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #21272c;\" rel=\"noopener\">Who is Black comedy for</a>? And <a href=\"https://link.theatlantic.com/click/45327773.55622/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlYXRsYW50aWMuY29tL21hZ2F6aW5lLzIwMjYvMDUvam9obi1tYXJrLWNvbWVyLXNwaXJpdHVhbC1wcmFjdGljZXMvNjg2NTg2Lz91dG1fbWVkaXVtPWNyJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9ZW1haWw/668d137112b797104109b7bcBcd5038da\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #21272c;\" rel=\"noopener\">can turning off your phone bring you closer to God</a>?&nbsp;</span>\r\n</p><p style=\"margin:0;font-size:18px;mso-line-height-alt:27px\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word; font-size: 18px;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin:0;font-size:18px;mso-line-height-alt:27px\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word; font-size: 18px;\">Read these, and more, <strong>in the</strong> <strong>May issue</strong> of <em>The Atlantic</em>.</span></p><p style=\"margin:0;font-size:18px;mso-line-height-alt:27px\"><span style=\"word-break: break-word; font-size: 18px;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p \r\nstyle=\"margin:0;font-size:18px;mso-line-height-alt:27px\">\r\n<span style=\"word-break: break-word; font-size: 18px;\"><em>Atlantic</em> subscribers enjoy 12 magazine issues every year, featuring some of our deepest reporting, stunning art and photography, and the monthly edition of Caleb's Inferno, the devilishly difficult word puzzle. Get the May issue today, along with unlimited access to all of <em>The Atlantic</em>, when you subscribe,<a href=\"https://link.theatlantic.com/click/45327773.55622/aHR0cHM6Ly9hY2NvdW50cy50aGVhdGxhbnRpYy5jb20vcHJvZHVjdHMvP3V0bV9tZWRpdW09Y3ImdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1lbWFpbA/668d137112b797104109b7bcFcd65f710\" target=\"_blank\"